'''Francis Schwitzgebel Torres''' (born 1957) is an [[England|English]]-[[Bolivia]]n writer, art critic, and artist born in [[Leeds]], England of Bolivian descent. Recently awarded with distinctions for her fiction in Bolivia's short story annual contest, [[Pedro Domingo Murillo]], and an honorary mention in the XV Santa Cruz Art Biennial. She is well known for her cultural, literary and art critiques published in diverse national media.
==External links== *[https://web.archive.org/web/20061231050807/http://www.lostiempos.com/lecturas/23-07-06/arte.php La Influencia del arte y el arte de la Influencia, Los Tiempos, Cochabamba, Bolivia, 2006] *[https://web.archive.org/web/20070928093221/http://www.lostiempos.com/lecturas/06-08-06/06_08_06_arte2.php Interview with Francis Schwitzgebel Torres, Las estrellas de la Literatura Boliviana, Los Tiempos, Cochabamba, Bolivia, 2006] *[https://web.archive.org/web/20070928061834/http://www.el-nuevodia.com/versiones/20061115_006920/nota_253_356804.htm Premio Franz Tamayo,El Nuevo Día, La Paz, 2006] *[https://web.archive.org/web/20061125080716/http://www.laprensa.com.bo/fondo_negro/20060820/art06.htm Karmacamaleónica,critique of Bolivian Writer Giovanna Rivero, Fondo Negro, La Paz, 2006] *https://web.archive.org/web/20061125080604/http://www.laprensa.com.bo/fondo_negro/20060806/art06.htm *[https://web.archive.org/web/20070106174721/http://www.mna.org.bo/actividades.html Siart Biennial, La Paz] *[https://web.archive.org/web/20070928172300/http://www.eldeber.com.bo/brujula/2007-01-20/nota.php?id=1805 Critique on XV Santa Cruz de la Sierra Biennial, El Deber, Santa Cruz, January 20th, 2007]
