{{Expand German|Peter Hammerschlag|date=December 2009}}
[[File:2018-07-18 Sterne der Satire - Walk of Fame des Kabaretts Nr 50 Peter Hammerschlag-1130.jpg|thumb|Hammerschlag's star at the Walk of Fame of Cabaret.]]
'''Peter Hammerschlag''' (27 June 1902, [[Alsergrund]], Vienna {{mdash}} 1942, [[Auschwitz concentration camp]]) was an Austrian writer, [[surrealism|surreal]]ist poet, actor, [[Kabarett]] artist and graphic artist. He was known for his [[cabaret]]s, which continue to influence the arts in Austria today,<ref>{{cite book|last = Mckenzie|first = John R. P.|author2=[[Lesley A. Sharpe]] |title= The Austrian Comic Tradition|year=1998|publisher=[[Edinburgh University Press]]|isbn= 0-7486-1086-3|authorlink= John R. P. Mckenzie}}</ref> and in 2007, but was honoured on the [[Walk of Fame of Cabaret]]. Hammerschlag was granted an exit permit to leave Austria for Argentina in September 1941, he was, however, unable to obtain a passport through any channels.<ref>{{cite book|last =Berger|first =Peter|authorlink =Peter Berger (historian) |editor=[[Terry Gourvish]] |title =The Gildemeester Organisation for Assistance t Emigrants and the expulsion of Jews from Vienna, 1938–1942 in Business and Politics in Europe, 1900–1970: Essays in Honour of [[Alice Teichova]]|publisher = Cambridge|year =2003|location =|pages =215–245|isbn =0-521-82344-7}}</ref> Later that year he was put into a [[forced labour camp]], and in 1942, he died in the [[Auschwitz concentration camp]].<ref name="Bohlman">{{cite book|last1=Bohlman|first1=Philip Vilas|last2=Gilman|first2=Sander L. |title=Jewish musical modernism, old and new, Volume 1|url=https://books.google.com/?id=D9Sll7BZyVIC&pg=PA183&dq=Peter+Hammerschlag+auschwitz#v=onepage&q=Peter%20Hammerschlag%20auschwitz&f=false|year=2008|publisher=[[University of Chicago Press]]|isbn=978-0-226-06326-3|page=183}}</ref> His work has been on display at the [[Jewish Museum Vienna|City of Vienna's Jewish Museum]].<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.nlib.ee/cenl/docs/annual_reports/austria97-98.pdf|title = AUSTRIAN NATIONAL LIBRARY: ANNUAL REPORT 1997|publisher = [[Austrian National Library]]|accessdate = June 10, 2008}}</ref>
